#### Interrupted Time Series Analysis (ITS) ####

# Author: Vitor Manuel B. Ferreira
# Description: General template for performing ITS analysis on any dataset.

## DATASET STRUCTURE ##

# 'time': numeric variable representing sequential time points. 
# It could be days, months, or years. For instance, January to December would be 1 to 12.

# 'treatment': binary variable indicating intervention (0 = before, 1 = after).

# 'time_since': time since the intervention. Values are 0 before the intervention and increase sequentially afterward.
# For instance, if the intervention occurred in time 5 (May), the four months before May would be = 0. 
# And then after the intervention, June = 1, July = 2, August = 3 to December = 7.

# 'response_variable': numeric variable(s) to analyze (can be multiple columns).

# Final model structure would be: response_variable ~ time + treatment + time_since, data = dataset

## REQUIRED PACKAGES ##

library(data.table)   # Efficient data handling
library(tidyverse)    # Data wrangling and visualization
library(nlme)         # GLS models for autocorrelation
library(ggplot2)      # Visualization
library(ggpubr)       # Arranging plots

